The sliding mode theory allows to design MPPT controller with a robust behavior in presence of external disturbances such as temperature and irradiance variations. This method consists in varying the state trajectory of the system to a predefined sliding surface [23, 36, 44]. This function is achieved by developing a control law which forces the output y=∂Ppv∂Vpv\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
